hop to hear firsthand from recruiters about what they’re looking for at the interview.       Navigating a Career Fair   Learn how to successfully navigate a career fair. Topics include  dressing professionally, bringing  plenty of updated resumes, researching employers in advance, preparing an elevator speech, and other valuable advice.       Not Able to Attend Workshops?   Come to Student Employment during Walk-In Hours,  call, or email to set up an appointment to discuss resumes, cover letters, interviews, or job search strategies.          Events    Back to main content           Webinars    Workshops    On Campus Job Fair    UIC Spring Internship & Part-Time Job Fair    National Student Employment Week (NSEW)     NSEW Sweet Sentiments Form                    UIC Logo        Student Employment         Quick Links    UIC Career Services    UIC Careers      For Students    Job Listings    JLD Program      For Departments    Forms    Job Descriptions    Student Wage Plan        Footer Menu    Students    Departments    UIC Careers    UIC Career Services         Contact   Suite 2100 1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, Illinois 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3130  Fax: (312) 413-7944  studentjobs@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 